## Ownership Methodology

Ownership was assigned from documented evidence only:

- primary nucleus in the Global Opportunity Registry;
- target nucleus in the Dependency Registry;
- Business L4 dependency, risk and governance frameworks;
- nucleus STATUS, HANDOFF, validation and maturity records;
- existing blocker and roadmap evidence.

When ownership was plausible but not explicit, it was recorded as medium confidence or listed as an ambiguity. No execution authority was assigned by inference.

## Readiness Methodology

Readiness uses the Business readiness model:

- 0 = Unknown / READINESS_UNKNOWN
- 1 = Draft / READINESS_DRAFT
- 2 = Assessed / READINESS_ASSESSED
- 3 = Approved / READINESS_APPROVED
- 4 = Ready / READINESS_READY

Readiness indicates planning or non-executive maturity only. It does not authorize production behavior.

## Nucleus Ownership Summary

Business is confirmed as the non-executive portfolio coordination owner. Core and Governance remain foundation/authority owners. Documentation owns publication governance. Dex owns read-only DEX provider readiness. Execution-sensitive ownership remains with the relevant product nuclei and is blocked until separate review.

## Opportunity Ownership Summary

All 25 official opportunities have primary owner, support owner, approval authority, execution owner, Business role, Governance role, readiness state and ownership confidence recorded in `/opt/Axodus/.instructions/AXODUS_OWNERSHIP_MATRIX.md`.

High-risk opportunity groups:

- Governance and voting products;
- Vault.Country and Defi Phase 3;
- Dex.Country execution-adjacent scope;
- Marketplace settlement;
- Academy rewards/certification;
- Mining payouts;
- Trading credential/execution gate;
- ACS execution authority;
- Lottery randomness/payout.

## Dependency Ownership Summary

All 58 official dependencies have dependency owner, consumer, responsible nucleus, escalation owner, blocking owner and resolution owner recorded in `/opt/Axodus/.instructions/AXODUS_OWNERSHIP_MATRIX.md`.

## Ownership Ambiguities

- Root portfolio docs are local/unversioned and lack a selected versioned owner.
- Treasury/Financial Core is referenced as an approval domain but not represented as a dedicated nucleus.
- Harmony DAO appears as an external support dependency but lacks an Axodus ownership record.
- Business-to-AxodusAPP transfer for future registry UI needs a read-only consumer contract.
- Wallet/account custody ownership crosses AxodusAPP, Core and product nuclei and remains blocked.

## Readiness Gaps

Critical gaps:

- Defi treasury/custody approval path;
- ACS execution authority;
- Trading credential/execution gate;
- Lottery compliance/randomness/payout;
- Marketplace settlement and treasury boundary.

High gaps:

- Governance execution gates;
- Documentation publication authority;
- Dex execution-adjacent treasury exposure;
- Academy rewards/certification;
- Mining provider/payout.

Medium gaps:

- AxodusAPP read-only consumer contracts;
- BBA schema/claim review;
- Core consumer pilot/RC evidence;
- Business/global registry versioning.

